1 WHEREAS, these federal environmental policies have harmed all North Dakotans by
2 reducing revenue by an estimated $1.2 billion to the state and royalties to mineral owners; and
3 WHEREAS, holding foreign polluters to the same standards as domestic producers would
4 provide a plethora of benefits to the state of North Dakota, including diversifying supply chains
5 by reducing the United States' dependence on imports from high-emitting producers like Russia
6 and China, decreasing global pollution by holding the biggest polluters accountable to western
7 environmental standards, and bolstering domestic manufacturing and generating well-paying
8 jobs in rural areas;
9 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF
10 NORTH DAKOTA, THE SENATE CONCURRING THEREIN:
11 That the Sixty-ninth Legislative Assembly urges the federal government to support trade
12 policies that hold high-polluting countries like China and Russia accountable for pollution and
13 bolster domestic extraction and production; and
14 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that the Secretary of State forward a copy of this resolution
15 to the President of the United States, the Speaker of the United States House of
16 Representatives, the President Pro Tempore of the United States Senate, and each member of
17 the North Dakota Congressional Delegation.
